name: r-yardstick
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-yardstick
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/yardstick_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/yardstick/yardstick_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: cd23cf232d140d8b9175d833cce4b291dfdbcf9275454ff821b72fff17dfd756

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.9
    - r-generics >=0.1.2
    - r-hardhat >=1.0.0
    - r-rlang >=1.0.2
    - r-tidyselect >=1.1.2
    - r-vctrs >=0.4.1
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.9
    - r-generics >=0.1.2
    - r-hardhat >=1.0.0
    - r-rlang >=1.0.2
    - r-tidyselect >=1.1.2
    - r-vctrs >=0.4.1

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('yardstick')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('yardstick')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/tidymodels/yardstick
  license: MIT
  summary: Tidy tools for quantifying how well model fits to a data set such as confusion matrices, class probability curve summaries, and regression metrics (e.g., RMSE).
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
